{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@gero3 Your new method  `getUpdatedMatrixWorld()` is quite clever, IMHO, and is a solution to a much larger issue.\n\n`getUpdatedMatrixWorld()` traverses up a single branch of the tree, and ignores the children of the object -- as it should. The method `updateMatrixWorld()`, on the other hand, traverses down the tree and updates the object's children.\n\nIf I am not mistaken, what we should do is (1) rename `updateMatrixWorld()` to something else, like `updateWorldMatrices()`, and (2) rename your new method to  `updateMatrixWorld()`.\n\nIf we did that, `scene.updateWorldMatrices()` would then be called by the renderer to traverse the scene graph, and your new version of `updateMatrixWorld()` would do what it should have been doing all along.\n\nThis will have no effect on users. Developers can call `updateMatrixWorld()` prior to referencing `object.MatrixWorld` in cases where the traversal would not be too burdensome.\n","created_at":"2015-04-23T15:24:58.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-95624064","id":95624064,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk1NjI0MDY0","updated_at":"2015-04-23T15:24:58.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/95624064","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Wow. Mind blown. So pretty :+1: \nAlso, what @WestLangley said!\n","created_at":"2015-04-23T21:15:37.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-95720640","id":95720640,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk1NzIwNjQw","updated_at":"2015-04-23T21:15:37.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/95720640","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"These are the places that needs to be checked if we rename.\n\n```\n\/src\/cameras\/CubeCamera.js:\n    50:         if ( this.parent === undefined ) this.updateMatrixWorld();\n\n\/src\/core\/Object3D.js:\n    414:        this.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n    429:            this.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n    464:            this.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n    538:    updateMatrixWorld: function ( force ) {\n    564:            this.children[ i ].updateMatrixWorld( force );\n\n\/src\/extras\/audio\/Audio.js:\n    122: THREE.Audio.prototype.updateMatrixWorld = ( function () {\n    128:        THREE.Object3D.prototype.updateMatrixWorld.call( this, force );\n\n\/src\/extras\/audio\/AudioListener.js:\n    18: THREE.AudioListener.prototype.updateMatrixWorld = ( function () {\n    28:         THREE.Object3D.prototype.updateMatrixWorld.call( this, force );\n\n\/src\/extras\/core\/Gyroscope.js:\n    14: THREE.Gyroscope.prototype.updateMatrixWorld = ( function () {\n    59:             this.children[ i ].updateMatrixWorld( force );\n\n\/src\/extras\/helpers\/DirectionalLightHelper.js:\n    12:     this.light.updateMatrixWorld();\n\n\/src\/extras\/helpers\/FaceNormalsHelper.js:\n    48:     object.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n\n\/src\/extras\/helpers\/HemisphereLightHelper.js:\n    11:     this.light.updateMatrixWorld();\n\n\/src\/extras\/helpers\/PointLightHelper.js:\n    9:  this.light.updateMatrixWorld();\n\n\/src\/extras\/helpers\/SpotLightHelper.js:\n    12:     this.light.updateMatrixWorld();\n\n\/src\/extras\/helpers\/VertexNormalsHelper.js:\n    53:         this.object.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n\n\/src\/extras\/helpers\/VertexTangentsHelper.js:\n    52:         this.object.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n\n\/src\/math\/Box3.js:\n    68:             object.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n\n\/src\/objects\/SkinnedMesh.js:\n    75:     this.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n    90:         this.updateMatrixWorld( true );\n    137: THREE.SkinnedMesh.prototype.updateMatrixWorld = function( force ) {\n    139:    THREE.Mesh.prototype.updateMatrixWorld.call( this, true );\n\n\/src\/renderers\/WebGLRenderer.js:\n    1634:       if ( scene.autoUpdate === true ) scene.updateMatrixWorld();\n    1638:       if ( camera.parent === undefined ) camera.updateMatrixWorld();\n\n\/src\/renderers\/webgl\/WebGLShadowMap.js:\n    204:                if ( scene.autoUpdate === true ) scene.updateMatrixWorld();\n    230:            shadowCamera.updateMatrixWorld();\n\nFound 28 matches in 16 files \n```\n","created_at":"2015-04-27T10:56:40.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-96609519","id":96609519,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk2NjA5NTE5","updated_at":"2015-04-27T10:56:40.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/96609519","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/155535?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/gero3","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1NTUzNQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"gero3","type":"User","id":155535,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/gero3\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Wait. Thinking about this a bit more...\n\nThis can break a ton of code out there. Anyone extending `Object3D` and doing their own `updateMatrixWorld()`...\n\nSorry about this @gero3 but I think it's better to revert to the original commit. Naming-wise `.getUpdatedMatrixWorld()` is probably ok, but how about `.traverseUpdateMatrixWorld()` or `.parentUpdateMatrixWorld()`?\n","created_at":"2015-04-27T14:26:41.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-96674599","id":96674599,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk2Njc0NTk5","updated_at":"2015-04-27T14:26:41.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/96674599","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@mrdoob I am not following you. The current version of `updateMatrixWord()` does not \"update\" `matrixWorld` because it does not update parents. Instead, it does something else. @gero3's new method does what `updateMatrixWord()` should be doing. We should fix it.\n","created_at":"2015-04-27T14:54:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-96684954","id":96684954,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk2Njg0OTU0","updated_at":"2015-04-27T14:54:22.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/96684954","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"@WestLangley Yes, I agree with that. The problem is that we should be careful on not breaking other people's code. With this change we're changing what `.updateMatrixWorld()` does (no longer updates the children) so this will be breaking the code of people that depend on the old behaviour.\n","created_at":"2015-04-27T15:07:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-96694616","id":96694616,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk2Njk0NjE2","updated_at":"2015-04-27T15:08:26.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/96694616","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@mrdoob  I hear you, but we are compelled to fix things that are not correct. I believe the benefits of this change outweigh the costs -- unless a performance study indicates otherwise.\n","created_at":"2015-04-27T15:30:14.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-96709538","id":96709538,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk2NzA5NTM4","updated_at":"2015-04-27T15:30:14.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/96709538","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"The problem is that by just changing the behaviour of a method we can't let the user know. One option would be to find new names for the methods and redirect with a warning.\n\nSomething like `.getUpdatedMatrixWorld()` and `.computeWorldMatrices()`. That way, if someone extends `updateMatrixWorld()` we can warn the user that they its been renamed to `.computeWorldMatrices()`.\n","created_at":"2015-04-27T23:23:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-96849527","id":96849527,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk2ODQ5NTI3","updated_at":"2015-04-27T23:23:54.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/96849527","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"OK. To cover all the bases, I think we only need the following two methods:\n\n`object.updateMatrix()` - updates `object.matrix` from `object.position`, `object.quaternion`, and `object.scale`. This method does not change.\n\n`object.updateWorldMatrix( recursive, force )` - updates `object.matrixWorld` using the approach proposed by @gero3. If `recursive` is true (it defaults to `false`), it also updates the world matrices of the object's children. (The `force` flag is something we may need -- may not... )\n\nSo, the renderer would call `scene.updateWorldMatrix( true )`. Users would be advised to use `updateWorldMatrix()` instead of `updateMatrixWorld()`.\n\n---\n\nAlternatively, we can keep things really simple, and keep the `updateMatrixWorld()` method -- just modify it so it traverses up the tree, too.\n","created_at":"2015-04-28T00:21:04.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/6448#issuecomment-96856178","id":96856178,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/6448","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDk2ODU2MTc4","updated_at":"2015-04-28T00:21:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/